commit.message: Support for string-style PEP 484 type annotations - fixes #84
Small cleanup for async nodes
Bugfix for parsing fstrings in multiple parts - fixes #66
Bugfix for namedexpr and unicode decoding in annotate_test

Support reading BOM at beginning of a module

Fixes #31

Add test for ast node support

Checks that there are not ast nodes which are unsupported, by checking
that there is a visit_<Node> function for each node type in the _ast
module.
Add support for positional only args in function definitions
Support for python 3.8 assignment expressions
Support for async/await syntax + python 3.7/3.8 tests
Sort ast nodes in constants + remove duplicates

Bugfix for determining indentation level of unformatted nodes

+ fix for detecting indentation level, which was possible to be None

Fixes #82
setup.py: Add url (#81)
Explicit tests for PEP 515; numbers with underscores

Support YieldFrom node (python3.3+)

+ add tests for Yield
Move out-of-place comment

Support keywords in ClassDef

Fixes #79.

Updating version to 0.1.8

+ add `six` to `install_requires` in setup.

Support mixing tabs and spaces in indentation level in python2 (#71)

* Support mixing tabs and spaces in indentation level in python2

Fixes #70.

* Rework the indent diffing algorithm to compute widths

A much more sensible approach, given inspiration from @ssbr.

* Fix tests to run on py2 only
